papers.title:
Mechanistic investigation of the denitrosylation activity of a water-soluble copper(
 ii
 ) compound probed by experimental and computational approaches

papers.abstract:
A water-soluble Cu(
ii
) compound promotes the denitrosylation of GSNO at room temperature and physiological pH. A reaction mechanism was proposed based on kinetic, spectroscopic, and spectrometric experiments, further supported by DFT calculations.
